<!-- Seventh question -->
<section id="about" class="container content-section text-center">
  <div class="row">
    <h2>
    I think that many Slovak developers would be aware of your gem "Thinking Sphinx". Personally, our company uses this gem in our project. Why did you decide to create this gem, instead of using other ones? Is search a personal interest of yours?
    </h2>
    <hr>
               
    <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2"> 
      <br> 
      <p>
      I wrote the first version of Thinking Sphinx over seven years ago - back then, Sphinx was one of the more popular search tools, but I felt the existing gems that integrated with it weren’t as elegant as they could be, so I spent a weekend writing Thinking Sphinx.
      </p>

      <p>
			Of course, I didn’t really understand Sphinx then, so I had to rewrite it several months later, and since then it’s evolved, had features added, and many bugs fixed. The first version was written to support Rails 1, and just the other week I made a patch to support Rails 4.2 - it’s come a long way!
      </p>
        
      <p>
      I’ve had to learn some broader concepts about search over the years - I wouldn’t say it’s been a personal interest of mine, and I don’t consider myself an expert in search! My interest has more been around how to write Ruby gems well, and how to integrate with other tools in a solid manner.
      </p>	                                 
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

